<TITLE> US and Poland sign missile shield deal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 WARSAW, Wed Aug 20,(bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The United States and Poland formally signed a deal on Wednesday to station elements of US missile defense on Polish soil, a move rising Russia-West tensions over Moscow's intervention in Georgia. The agreement was signed by US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice and her Polish counterpart Radoslaw Sikorski at a ceremony also attended by Polish Prime Minister Donald Tusk and President Lech Kaczynski. Russia has called the deal a threat to its security and accused Warsaw and Washington of hastening its signing as a response to its military action in Georgia
